## Email Template Structure

### Every Email Contains

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Logo / Brand header                │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                     │
│  Greeting: "Hi {{firstName}},"      │
│                                     │
│  Body: Clear, concise copy          │
│  explaining what happened and       │
│  what action to take (if any).      │
│                                     │
│  ┌──────────────────────┐           │
│  │   Primary Action     │           │ <- single CTA button
│  └──────────────────────┘           │
│                                     │
│  Fallback: plain-text link below    │
│  the button for email clients       │
│  that don't render buttons.         │
│                                     │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Footer:                            │
│  - Company name / address           │
│  - Unsubscribe link (REQUIRED)    │
│  - User preferences endpoint link  │
│  - "Why am I getting this?" note    │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Rules

- **Plain text version** for every HTML email (some clients strip HTML)
- **Responsive** - test on major clients and mobile
- **Single primary CTA** per email - don't overwhelm with multiple actions
- **Sender name** is recognizable: "AppName" or "Team at AppName" - not "noreply"
- **Reply-to** set to a monitored address (even if the from address is noreply@)
- **Subject line** is clear, specific, and under 50 characters:
  - "Action required: [short description]" not "Update"
  - "Your [resource] has been updated" not "Something changed"
- **Preheader text** (preview text) supplements the subject - not a repeat of it
- **No images for critical info** - some email clients block images; copy must be readable without them
- **Contrast** - ensure text/background contrast is readable across common client rendering modes

