## Email Sending Architecture

```
App Event -> Dispatch Service -> Queue -> Email Worker -> SMTP Provider -> Inbox

Components:
  1. Dispatch Service      - decides what to send, to whom, on which channel
  2. Subscriber preferences - checks if the subscriber wants this category/channel
  3. Template Renderer      - builds HTML + plain text from template + data
  4. Queue                  - async job queue (don't send in the request cycle)
  5. Email Worker           - pulls from queue, sends via SMTP/API
  6. SMTP Provider          - SendGrid, AWS SES, Mailgun, etc.
  7. Delivery Tracking      - bounce, open, click tracking
```

### Rules

- **Queue emails** instead of sending synchronously in the API request handler - "send immediately" above means the queue processes it right away, not that you block the API response
- **Retry failed sends** - 3 retries with exponential backoff (1min, 5min, 30min)
- **Handle bounces** - mark email as invalid after hard bounce; suppress future sends
- **Process opt-outs** - handle unsubscribe webhooks from the email provider
- **Rate limit outbound email** - respect provider limits; follow deliverability best practices
- **Log every email sent** - recipient (masked), template, timestamp, delivery status
- **Test with real provider** in staging (not just console.log) - verify formatting before production

