## Subscriber Preference Grid Pattern (IF your app has preference UI)

**Principle:** Users should control which notifications they receive and through which channels. Provide granular opt-out.

[REFERENCE] Common notification channel matrix:

```
Category / channel        In-App    Push    Email    SMS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Critical / Security       yes *       yes       yes *     yes
  (cannot disable)
Category A                yes         yes       yes       off
Category B                yes         yes       yes       off
Category C                yes         yes       off       off
Low-frequency summaries   n/a         n/a       yes       n/a

yes = on by default    off = off by default    * = mandatory (cannot disable)    n/a = not applicable
```

### Rules

- **Security-sensitive events** are always sent by default - subscribers should not be able to opt out of critical security alerts
- **Sensible defaults** - don't enable everything by default; avoid long opt-out checklists
- **Per-channel granularity** - let subscribers choose email vs push vs in-app per category
- **Batch frequent updates** - batched updates beat many near-duplicate emails in a short window
- **Quiet hours** - respect "do not disturb" settings (don't send push at 3 AM)
- **Unsubscribe from email** - one-click unsubscribe in every bulk-capable send; comply with applicable regulations for bulk sending

