## Email Template Management

```
Template storage:
  Option A: In-code templates (version controlled, deployed with app)
    templates/
    ├── template-a.html
    ├── template-a.txt
    ├── template-b.html
    ├── template-b.txt
    └── ... (one pair per template id)

  Option B: Email provider's template system (managed in their console)
    Pro: Non-developers can edit
    Con: Not version controlled, harder to test

Recommended: Option A for critical transactional templates; Option B acceptable for large bulk programs if governance allows.
```

### Template Variables

```
Every template has access to:
  {{appName}}           - "MyApp"
  {{appUrl}}            - "https://myapp.com"
  {{recipientName}}     - "Pat"
  {{recipientEmail}}    - "pat@example.com"
  {{currentYear}}       - "2024"
  {{unsubscribeUrl}}    - one-click unsubscribe link
  {{preferencesUrl}}    - user preferences endpoint URL

Plus template-specific variables (whatever your feature needs):
  e.g., {{actionUrl}}, {{expiryHours}}, {{entityTitle}}, {{actorName}}
```

